snippet.textDisplay: I am widow who is receiving my beloved disabled husband social security income who passed away on 1/8/2019.  Our 2 adult children with disabilities were receiving SSI until after he passed they now receive disability adult children social security income. Since both of them worked our oldest son age 25 worked for 3 months a paid TWE with DVR and our daughter got job July 2019 who was working up until March 20, 2020. Son hasn’t found a job since May 2019. So I did there taxes March 29, 2020 they both got tax returns so I was able to put there direct deposit in there e-file and both already got there federal direct deposit today, son got his Wisconsin state tax on this past Monday. But my daughter got a letter from state of Wisconsin so had to contact them to proof of identity with the special codes in the letter. She still hasn’t gotten the WI state check of $45 which isn’t much but I called the same day it came last week Friday. Ok down to myself. In 2018 when our daughter was still in high school and still our dependent I check my tax return that I did on HR Block and I did indeed put her on our 2018 taxes. But didn’t include any direct deposit info. But that clause if you didn’t do your 2019 taxes yet they would go by what you claim in 2018. So I was able to file e-file March 28, 2020 for 2019 taxes without her as our dependent, I was still able to claim us as married as I contacted someone on HR Block chat. I wish I knew that I needed to add our direct deposit info even if we didn’t have to pay anything or owe anything. Otherwise I would of done it. But found this out after I had done my taxes I believe it came out on or after April 1st. My question to you would this delay getting this stimulus if they can get our info from social security 1099 form? Would I only be entitled to just the $1,200 or for a married couple the $2,400? Just want to know if our adult children get there’s next week and I don’t should I worry about it or wait to see if I need to add my direct deposit or would it take extra week for them to get it from social security? Sorry for the long detail info but best to know our story.

snippet.textDisplay: Social Security and Railroad Retirement recipients who are not typically required to file a tax return need to take no action. The IRS will use the information on the Form SSA-1099 and Form RRB-1099 to generate Economic Impact Payments of $1,200 to these individuals even if they did not file tax returns in 2018 or 2019. Recipients will receive these payments as a direct deposit or by paper check, just as they would normally receive their benefits. Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI) recipients are also part of this group who don't need to take action.

Senate Minority Leader Charles Schumer (D-N.Y.) and other Democrats are proposing to give doctors, nurses and other essential workers, such as grocery store clerks, up to $25,000 in hazard pay as part of the phase four coronavirus relief bill.
The bonus pay, which would amount to a $13-per-hour raise, would also go to truck drivers and janitors, who Democrats say are also essential to keeping the health care system and economy running during the crisis.
It would stretch from the start of the public health emergency to the end of the year.
